thread.title_full: Local sports briefs for Oct. 10: WU volleyball rolls past Fort Hays State

author: The Capital-Journal
title: Local sports briefs for Oct. 10: WU volleyball rolls past Fort Hays State
text:
By The Capital-Journal 
The No. 12 Washburn Ichabod volleyball team defeated Fort Hays State 3-1 (14-25, 25-17, 25-17, 25-19) on Saturday in Hays. 
Three WU players, Korie Thompson, Leanna Willer and Sarah Vicory, recorded double-digit kills to lead the Ichabods (18-2, 6-2 MIAA) to victory over FHSU. 
Washburn begins a four-game homestand at 7 p.m. Friday against Northwest Missouri. 
SCHULTEJANS LEADS K-STATE VOLLEYBALL PAST WEST VIRGINIA: Kansas State volleyball, led by freshman Alyssa Schultejans, swept West Virginia to maintain a perfect home record on Saturday in Manhattan. 
Schultejans, a former Silver Lake standout, recorded 12 kills in the Wildcats’ victory. Five K-State players tallied six or more kills to lift the Wildcats to 5-0 at Bramlage Colosseum this season. 
K-State (10-7, 2-3 Big 12) will hit the road for a matchup with Oklahoma at 6 p.m. Friday. 
ROADRUNNERS DROP SECOND TO ODESSA: The Topeka RoadRunners were unable to overcome the Odessa Jackalopes on Saturday, falling 4-2 to their South Division rival. 
Odessa scored three times in the first two periods before the RoadRunners were able to get on the board with a Ryan O’Connor goal 4:21 into the third period. Dominic Lutz scored nearly two minutes later off a Tyler Hays assist to bring Topeka within one score. 
The RoadRunners were unable to capitalize, and gave up their final goal with 54 seconds left in the game. 
Topeka (6-6) will return home to face the Springfield Blues at 7 p.m. Friday.
